# Persistence — cache, persist, StorageLevel

## The default is wasteful

- **Every action re-runs the whole lineage** from source
- `.count()` then `.collect()` on the same RDD = computed **twice**

## Fix it

- **`.cache()`** — materialize on first action, reuse after
- **`.persist(level)`** — pick the storage policy:
  - **`MEMORY_ONLY`** — RAM; default for `.cache()` on RDDs
  - **`MEMORY_AND_DISK`** — RAM then spill; default for DataFrames
  - **`DISK_ONLY`** · **`*_SER`** (less RAM, more CPU) · **`*_2`** (replicate ×2)

## Clean up

- **`.unpersist()`** when done — a cache holds executor memory until released
